headline: SNA Q1 Earnings Call: Revenue Miss and Margin Pressure Amid Technician Uncertainty
summary: Professional tools and equipment manufacturer Snap-on (NYSE:SNA) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales falling 3% year on year to $1.24 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.51 per share was 6.3% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
